briefdescription.para: Directly decode Avro data to Arrow array builders without GenericDatum.

detaileddescription.para: Eliminates the GenericDatum intermediate layer by directly calling Avro decoder methods and immediately appending to Arrow builders. Matches Java Iceberg's ValueReader approach for better performance.

Features:
All primitive, temporal, and logical types
Nested types (struct, list, map)
Union types with bounds checking
Field skipping for schema projection
Schema Evolution: Schema resolution is handled via SchemaProjection (from Project() function). Supports field reordering and missing fields (set to NULL). Default values are NOT currently supported.

Error Handling:
Type mismatches → InvalidArgument
Union branch out of range → InvalidArgument
Decimal precision insufficient → InvalidArgument
Missing logical type → InvalidArgument

parameterdescription.para: The Avro schema node for the data being decoded
The Avro decoder positioned at the data to read
The field projections (from Project() function)
The target Iceberg schema after projection
The Arrow array builder to append decoded data to
Decode context for reusing scratch buffers

simplesect.para: Status::OK if successful, or an error status

Check if a string is a valid Avro name.

detaileddescription.para:
Valid Avro names must:
Start with a letter or underscore
Contain only letters, digits, or underscores

parameterdescription.para: The name to check.

simplesect.para: True if the name is valid, false otherwise.

briefdescription.para: Sanitize a field name to make it compatible with Avro field name requirements.

detaileddescription.para:
Converts names that are not valid Avro names to valid Avro names. Conversion rules:
If the first character is not a letter or underscore, it is specially handled:
Digits: Prefixed with an underscore (e.g., '3' -> '_3')
Other characters: Converted to '_x' followed by the uppercase hexadecimal representation of the character (e.g., '$' -> '_x24')
For characters other than the first:
If it's a letter, digit, or underscore, it remains unchanged
Other characters: Converted to '_x' followed by the uppercase hexadecimal representation

parameterdescription.para: The original field name to sanitize.

simplesect.para: A sanitized field name that follows Avro naming conventions.
